description: Tom Spilsbury is the current editor of Doctor Who Magazine. He is the thirteenth editor to take on the role
name: Tom Spilsbury

description: Alan O'Keefe was Managing Editor of Doctor Who Magazine for a number of issues. He later became Managing Editor of Doctor Who Insider.
name: Alan O'Keefe

description: Mark Irvine was a producer for Doctor Who Classic Comics. He later became Head of Production for Doctor Who Insider.
name: Mark Irvine

description: Pixley is a consultant for Doctor Who Classic Comics and has written installments of BBC Audio's Doctor Who at the BBC series.
name: Andrew Pixley

description: Benjamin Cook is a writer and interviewer for Doctor Who Magazine. Between 2007 and 2008, Cook collaborated with Russell T Davies on the 2008 book release Doctor Who: The Writer's Tale, which was issued in an expanded second edition subtitled The Final Chapter in 2010.
name: Benjamin Cook

description: John Ainsworth is a producer, director, script-editor and occasional voice actor for Big Finish Productions. He was also the editor of Doctor Who Insider, and appeared in Auton from BBV Productions, as well as the Reeltime Pictures production, The Corridor Sketch.
name: John Ainsworth

description: Gary Gillatt was an editor for Doctor Who Magazine who has also produced covers for Big Finish's Doctor Who Line. He also wrote Doctor Who: From A to Z. He returned to Doctor Who Magazine in 2008 to review the classic series DVDs each issue.
name: Gary Gillatt

description: Russell T Davies (born Stephen Russell Davies) is responsible for the revival of Doctor Who and the creation of two spin-off series, Torchwood and The Sarah Jane Adventures. From 2005 to mid-2009, he was the head writer and an executive producer of Doctor Who.
name: Russell T Davies

description: Dan Goldsmith was a photographer for the Radio Times.
name: Dan Goldsmith

description: Steven Moffat wrote numerous Doctor Who episodes, undertaking the position of head writer at the beginning of the Eleventh Doctor era. He is also currently the executive producer on the series.
name: Steven Moffat

deck: Chunn is an artist living in California who has done sketch work, painting, photography, and other art forms.
name: Steven Chunn

deck: Character designer at 5th Cell, creators of Scribblenauts
description: Katz illustrated homage variant covers for many DC Comics book during their 2014 themed Scribblenauts Unmasked variant covers promotion .
name: Jon Katz

deck: Orion Jerwa is a comic writer living in Seattle, WA. He made his comics debut (co-writing the PANTHA strip in Dynamite's LI'L VAMPI one-shot) at the age of 14. He is the son of writer Brandon Jerwa.
name: Orion Jerwa

deck: Mike Bunt is an artist living in the UK. He has worked on such comics as Deadroots, The Last Ride Of Henry Holden and various short stories for different publishers, some of which include: Future Quake, Drokk!, V.S comics and Black Hearted Press
name: Mike Bunt

deck: An American actor most well known for his role as Superman in the 2006 film Superman Returns.
description:
Comic Related Movie Roles

Superman

Routh played the iconic role as the Man of Steel in Superman Returns, set in continuity with the Christopher Reeve Superman, and Superman II films. In this film, Superman has finally returned to Earth after a five year trip into space to search the the remains of the exploded planet Krypton.

Ray Palmer

Routh will also make an Appearance in the television show Arrow as Ray Palmer, who is known as the character of Atom in the comics.
name: Brandon Routh
